Yuncheng salt lake in north China's Shanxi Province is an ancient inland salt lake. Formed about 500 million years ago, it is the world's third largest sodium sulphate inland lake. The water in the lake turns to orange and red with high salinity. The Colors of Nature This series combines music, color and natural scenery to give viewers a sensory experience. For more: Snowy Kanas in NW China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region The beauty of yellow sand The beauty of the color black The beauty of the color brown Do you like the color green? The beauty of yellow leaves The Colors of Nature: Pink peach flowers in Tibet The Colors of Nature: The yellow waterfall (Cover images via CFP) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)